#: ../restored/spotlights.rst:9
msgid "Spotlights"
msgstr ""

#: ../restored/spotlights.rst:11
msgid ""
"Spotlights are now available to all of the Big Four types, not just "
":type:`BuildingTypes`. When attached to a :type:`BuildingType`, the "
"spotlight still behaves like it used to, just circling around, but when "
"it is attached to a different unit type, such as a :type:`VehicleType`, "
"it is fixed to shine straight ahead."
msgstr ""

#: ../restored/spotlights.rst:17
msgid ""
"Spotlights would cause an Internal Error whenever they were created. The "
"error no longer occurs so spotlights can now be used."
msgstr ""

#: ../restored/spotlights.rst:20
msgid ""
"If an object with a spotlight cloaked, the spotlight was removed and "
"would not reappear once the object uncloaked. This doesn't happen "
"anymore. The spotlight will be invisible while the object is cloaked, "
"deactivated, being warped out, or burrowed, though."
msgstr ""

#: ../restored/spotlights.rst:26
msgid ":tagdef:`[TechnoType]HasSpotlight=boolean`"
msgstr ""

#: ../restored/spotlights.rst:26
msgid ""
"If set to :value:`yes`, creates a spotlight from the unit or structure. "
"Defaults to :value:`no`."
msgstr ""

#: ../restored/spotlights.rst:29
msgid ":tagdef:`[TechnoType]Spotlight.StartHeight=integer - leptons`"
msgstr ""

#: ../restored/spotlights.rst:29
msgid ""
"Specifies the number of leptons above the ground at which the spotlight "
"will be generated. Has to be :value:`0` or greater. Defaults to "
":value:`430`."
msgstr ""

#: ../restored/spotlights.rst:32
msgid ":tagdef:`[TechnoType]Spotlight.Distance=integer - leptons`"
msgstr ""

#: ../restored/spotlights.rst:32
msgid ""
"The number of leptons ahead of the unit where the spotlight will reach "
"the ground. Defaults to :value:`1024`."
msgstr ""

#: ../restored/spotlights.rst:38
msgid ""
":tagdef:`[TechnoType]Spotlight.AttachedTo=enumeration - one of "
"body|turret`"
msgstr ""

#: ../restored/spotlights.rst:35
msgid ""
"The part of the unit that the spotlight will align to in regards to "
"facing. If set to :value:`body` then the spotlight will be pointed in the"
" direction the unit's body is facing, if set to :value:`turret` then the "
"spotlight will be pointed in the direction the unit's turret is facing. "
"Does not work on :type:`BuildingTypes`. Defaults to :value:`body`."
msgstr ""

